<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="777" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/186:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-02T21:00:00+01:00">January 2,
                                    1943—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 2—7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8. My 922, December 30.<note n="15" xml:id="d777fn15">Not printed.</note>
                            Major Bernadoni<note n="16" xml:id="d777fn16">Maj. Bernard Bernadoni,
                                Assistant Military Attaché at the Legation in Tangier.</note> was
                            informed today by the officer in Tetuán in charge of our internees that
                            orders had <pb facs="0742" n="730" xml:id="pg_730"/> been received for
                            the sending of 17 of them to Madrid by a plane which had arrived for
                            that purpose. It was added the 17 are to be turned over to our Embassy
                            in Madrid for repatriation. The 17 include 9 officers at Melilla and the
                            ranking officer at Xauen who will be the first to be sent to Madrid by
                            the plane which can only carry 10 at a time. Departure will depend upon
                            the weather.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Madrid.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>